<taxonomicName id="27707A93DCC92870FFD32E733BDAE865" LSID="26C7DFE0-BAF7-582C-8A09-4F7F186C2128" authority="D. R. Hunt, Kew Bull. 35 (2): 440. 1980." authorityName="D. R. Hunt, Kew Bull. 35 (2): 440. 1980." class="Liliopsida" family="Commelinaceae" genus="Tradescantia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Tradescantia subsp. sect." order="Commelinales" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="section" section="Austrotradescantia" species="valida" subSpecies="sect.">Tradescantia sect. Austrotradescantia D.R.Hunt, Kew Bull. 35(2): 440. 1980.</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="0DD2ABE6C07C5C6EDA6C3733442EB08C" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="57FABA6238BB67B9B3123B411C56396E" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="76E7F93AE650C76BB727E802DF492065" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">
The section is characterized by perennial herbs, with thin and fibrous roots, definite or indefinite base, rhizomes absent, leaves with asymmetric base, inflorescences terminal or at the apex of the stems, pedunculate, cincinni bracts leaf-like or rarely spathaceous, bracteoles inconspicuous, flowers flat, sepals equal, free, generally keeled, petals free, sessile, stamens 6 and equal, free, filaments straight at post-anthesis, basally densely bearded with long moniliform hairs, connectives rhomboid, anther sacs elliptic, ovary glabrous, stigma punctate, seeds costate, rarely rugose, embryotega inconspicuous and dorsal (
<bibRefCitation id="5FB5A4C9766AE87AE45BCBD1F9EFDB20" DOI="https://doi.org/10.12705/641.3" author="Pellegrini, MOO" journalOrPublisher="Instituto de Biologia, Universidade Federal do Rio de Janeiro, Rio de Janeiro, Brazil" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" refId="B29" refString="Pellegrini, MOO, 2015. Filogenia e revisao taxonomica de Tradescantia L. sect. Austrotradescantia D.R.Hunt (Commelinaceae). In: MsC thesis. Instituto de Biologia, Universidade Federal do Rio de Janeiro, Rio de Janeiro, Brazil, DOI: https://doi.org/10.12705/641.3" title="Filogenia e revisao taxonomica de Tradescantia L. sect. Austrotradescantia D. R. Hunt (Commelinaceae)" url="https://doi.org/10.12705/641.3" volumeTitle="MsC thesis." year="2015">Pellegrini 2015</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="6DE4AB199B4886BFE811EF6E38FE0614" DOI="https://doi.org/10.1600/036364416X694053" author="Pellegrini, MOO" journalOrPublisher="Systematic Botany" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" pagination="950 - 958" refId="B33" refString="Pellegrini, MOO, Forzza, RC, Sakuragui, CM, 2016. (Con)Fused bracts: The identity and application of Tradescantia cymbispatha C.B.Clarke (Commelinaceae) and a neglected new Tradescantia species from Bolivia. Systematic Botany 41 (4): 950 - 958, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1600/036364416X694053" title="(Con) Fused bracts: The identity and application of Tradescantia cymbispatha C. B. Clarke (Commelinaceae) and a neglected new Tradescantia species from Bolivia." url="https://doi.org/10.1600/036364416X694053" volume="41" year="2016">Pellegrini et al. 2016</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="2089037E6923B7DEA2920F872FF8FF94" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" type="comments">
<paragraph id="92757317968F7B646DDAFC73FE39B12B" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Comments.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="F8B149BF060C6F9678959A6231F24681" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">
<taxonomicName id="AF0BCA2C34CDE3E9461D575BE3307E46" class="Liliopsida" family="Commelinaceae" genus="Tradescantia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Tradescantia subsp. sect." order="Commelinales" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="section" section="Austrotradescantia" species="valida" subSpecies="sect.">Tradescantia sect. Austrotradescantia</taxonomicName>
has been the subject of several recent studies (
<bibRefCitation id="D066490DC1BDB11BBEBCA5D9E3FA12A1" DOI="https://doi.org/10.12705/641.3" author="Pellegrini, MOO" journalOrPublisher="Instituto de Biologia, Universidade Federal do Rio de Janeiro, Rio de Janeiro, Brazil" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" refId="B29" refString="Pellegrini, MOO, 2015. Filogenia e revisao taxonomica de Tradescantia L. sect. Austrotradescantia D.R.Hunt (Commelinaceae). In: MsC thesis. Instituto de Biologia, Universidade Federal do Rio de Janeiro, Rio de Janeiro, Brazil, DOI: https://doi.org/10.12705/641.3" title="Filogenia e revisao taxonomica de Tradescantia L. sect. Austrotradescantia D. R. Hunt (Commelinaceae)" url="https://doi.org/10.12705/641.3" volumeTitle="MsC thesis." year="2015">Pellegrini 2015</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="5357107A25EF6C0B2D1E945C857C0FDC" author="Pellegrini, MOO" journalOrPublisher="Phytotaxa" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" pagination="79 - 84" refId="B30" refString="Pellegrini, MOO, 2016. A new species of Tradescantia L. sect. Austrotradescantia D.R.Hunt (Commelinaceae) from Southern Brazil. Phytotaxa 265 (1): 79 - 84" title="A new species of Tradescantia L. sect. Austrotradescantia D. R. Hunt (Commelinaceae) from Southern Brazil." volume="265" year="2016">2016</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="35929F6B2FFA700EDD00D4AF5EAE66EC" author="Pellegrini, MOO" journalOrPublisher="Jardim Botanico do Rio de Janeiro" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" publicationUrl="http://floradobrasil.jbrj.gov.br/reflora/floradobrasil/FB126851" refId="B31" refString="Pellegrini, MOO, 2017. Tradescantia. Flora do Brasil 2020 em construcao. Jardim Botanico do Rio de Janeiro, http://floradobrasil.jbrj.gov.br/reflora/floradobrasil/FB126851" title="Tradescantia. Flora do Brasil 2020 em construcao" url="http://floradobrasil.jbrj.gov.br/reflora/floradobrasil/FB126851" year="2017">2017</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="CACC4DD1AD23349B666449A3D6364268" author="Pellegrini, MOO" journalOrPublisher="Taxon" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" pagination="151 - 155" refId="B32" refString="Pellegrini, MOO, Forzza, RC, Sakuragui, CM, 2015. A nomenclatural and taxonomic review of Tradescantia L. (Commelinaceae) species described in Vellozo's Flora fluminensis with notes on Brazilian Tradescantia. Taxon 64 (1): 151 - 155" title="A nomenclatural and taxonomic review of Tradescantia L. (Commelinaceae) species described in Vellozo's Flora fluminensis with notes on Brazilian Tradescantia." volume="64" year="2015">Pellegrini et al. 2015</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="F22EE28386CB926F5F010BD1ED82FCD0" DOI="https://doi.org/10.1600/036364416X694053" author="Pellegrini, MOO" journalOrPublisher="Systematic Botany" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" pagination="950 - 958" refId="B33" refString="Pellegrini, MOO, Forzza, RC, Sakuragui, CM, 2016. (Con)Fused bracts: The identity and application of Tradescantia cymbispatha C.B.Clarke (Commelinaceae) and a neglected new Tradescantia species from Bolivia. Systematic Botany 41 (4): 950 - 958, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1600/036364416X694053" title="(Con) Fused bracts: The identity and application of Tradescantia cymbispatha C. B. Clarke (Commelinaceae) and a neglected new Tradescantia species from Bolivia." url="https://doi.org/10.1600/036364416X694053" volume="41" year="2016">2016</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="08FE92109BC27D08BD73AFF38F9B2F2E" DOI="https://doi.org/10.11646/phytotaxa.272.1.3" author="Funez, LA" journalOrPublisher="Phytotaxa" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" pagination="63 - 72" refId="B11" refString="Funez, LA, Hassemer, G, Ferreira, JPR, 2016. Description of Tradescantia schwirkowskiana (Commelinaceae), a narrow endemic new species from Santa Catarina, Southern Brazil, and typification of T. crassula. Phytotaxa 272 (1): 63 - 72, DOI: https://doi.org/10.11646/phytotaxa.272.1.3" title="Description of Tradescantia schwirkowskiana (Commelinaceae), a narrow endemic new species from Santa Catarina, Southern Brazil, and typification of T. crassula." url="https://doi.org/10.11646/phytotaxa.272.1.3" volume="272" year="2016">Funez et al. 2016</bibRefCitation>
). Species diversity in this section is centered in Southeastern and Southern Brazil, where all of the accepted species occur. However, some species in the group have a wider distribution, reaching neighboring countries like Argentina, Bolivia, Paraguay, and Uruguay (
<bibRefCitation id="8A0E73711EA09EFB376053F261166F2D" DOI="https://doi.org/10.12705/641.3" author="Pellegrini, MOO" journalOrPublisher="Instituto de Biologia, Universidade Federal do Rio de Janeiro, Rio de Janeiro, Brazil" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" refId="B29" refString="Pellegrini, MOO, 2015. Filogenia e revisao taxonomica de Tradescantia L. sect. Austrotradescantia D.R.Hunt (Commelinaceae). In: MsC thesis. Instituto de Biologia, Universidade Federal do Rio de Janeiro, Rio de Janeiro, Brazil, DOI: https://doi.org/10.12705/641.3" title="Filogenia e revisao taxonomica de Tradescantia L. sect. Austrotradescantia D. R. Hunt (Commelinaceae)" url="https://doi.org/10.12705/641.3" volumeTitle="MsC thesis." year="2015">Pellegrini 2015</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="085D1D1979E477CA7E2D83CD1C0C6AFD" DOI="https://doi.org/10.1600/036364416X694053" author="Pellegrini, MOO" journalOrPublisher="Systematic Botany" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" pagination="950 - 958" refId="B33" refString="Pellegrini, MOO, Forzza, RC, Sakuragui, CM, 2016. (Con)Fused bracts: The identity and application of Tradescantia cymbispatha C.B.Clarke (Commelinaceae) and a neglected new Tradescantia species from Bolivia. Systematic Botany 41 (4): 950 - 958, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1600/036364416X694053" title="(Con) Fused bracts: The identity and application of Tradescantia cymbispatha C. B. Clarke (Commelinaceae) and a neglected new Tradescantia species from Bolivia." url="https://doi.org/10.1600/036364416X694053" volume="41" year="2016">Pellegrini et al. 2016</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName id="CFA5243850F213075DFC42D53D3FDE63" class="Liliopsida" family="Commelinaceae" genus="Tradescantia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Tradescantia subsp. sect." order="Commelinales" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="section" section="Austrotradescantia" species="valida" subSpecies="sect.">Tradescantia sect. Austrotradescantia</taxonomicName>
has recently been revised, and its morphology thoroughly analyzed in a yet unpublished MSc thesis (
<bibRefCitation id="1A0D93C836B73A27F4CBB8D6EF594D87" DOI="https://doi.org/10.12705/641.3" author="Pellegrini, MOO" journalOrPublisher="Instituto de Biologia, Universidade Federal do Rio de Janeiro, Rio de Janeiro, Brazil" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" refId="B29" refString="Pellegrini, MOO, 2015. Filogenia e revisao taxonomica de Tradescantia L. sect. Austrotradescantia D.R.Hunt (Commelinaceae). In: MsC thesis. Instituto de Biologia, Universidade Federal do Rio de Janeiro, Rio de Janeiro, Brazil, DOI: https://doi.org/10.12705/641.3" title="Filogenia e revisao taxonomica de Tradescantia L. sect. Austrotradescantia D. R. Hunt (Commelinaceae)" url="https://doi.org/10.12705/641.3" volumeTitle="MsC thesis." year="2015">Pellegrini 2015</bibRefCitation>
). As part of our revision of this section, we describe a new species, report the rediscovery and inclusion of 
<taxonomicName id="13777EB845B1CADD07649C592945987C" genus="T." lsidName="T. valida" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" rank="species" species="valida">
<emphasis id="76A7B744C8AF762DC081904F8861D737" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">T. valida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the section, and a new synonym for 
<taxonomicName id="64003ADEA58BB893A2056ACC1CE24E44" genus="T." lsidName="T. crassula" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" rank="species" species="crassula">
<emphasis id="EFC5970CBE3978581DE91624E314D0AF" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">T. crassula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(with a correction of its typification).
</paragraph>
